In a #bowl{}, combine the @lamb mince{200%g}, @Middle Eastern style spice mix{1%tsp} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @black pepper{pinch}. Shape into 3-4 meatballs per person.

> TIP: Make sure the meatballs are rolled well so that they stick together!

> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands after handling raw meat!

Heat a splash of @oil{splash} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. When hot, add the meatballs. Fry until browned all over, turning frequently, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve the @green pepper{1}, remove the core and seeds and chop into 2cm chunks.

When the meatballs are browned, add the pepper and half the @cumin seeds{1/2%tsp}. Stir-fry for ~{3%minutes}, until the pepper has softened. Pour in the @tomatoes with onion and garlic{1}(finely chopped), half the @chicken stock powder{1}, @water for the sauce{100%ml} and bring to the boil. Stir, reduce the heat, cover the pan with a #lid{} or #foil{} and simmer for ~{15-20%minutes}. Stir occasionally.

Meanwhile, heat a large #saucepan{} over medium heat and add the remaining @cumin seeds{1/2%tsp} (no oil). Toast in the pan for ~{2%minutes}, then add the @basmati rice{150%g}, @water for the rice{300%ml} and remaining @chicken stock powder{1}. Stir and bring to the boil, reduce the heat to medium-low and cover with a lid. Cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove from the heat and set aside (still covered) for another ~{10%minutes}.

> TIP: The rice will finish cooking in its own steam.

Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all) and keep to one side. Quickly do any washing up that needs doing.

When the meatballs have been cooking for 15 minutes, remove the lid or foil, increase the heat to medium-high and leave to bubble away until the sauce is thick and tomatoey, another ~{5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The meatballs are cooked when they are no longer pink in the middle.

Once the rice is cooked, fluff it up with a #fork{} and stir through half the coriander. Share between your #bowls{}. Reheat the meatball stew if necessary and spoon on top of the cumin rice. Finish with a sprinkling of remaining coriander. Enjoy!